litical party)/meta/color}}}}\n| colorcode = {{Vox (political party)/meta/color}}\n| website = {{url|www.voxespana.es}}\n}}\n\n'''Vox''' ([[Latin]] for \"voice\", often stylized as '''VOX'''; {{IPA-es|\u02c8boks}}) is a [[list of political parties in Spain|political party in Spain]] founded on 17 December 2013, by former members of the [[People's Party (Spain)|People's Party]] (PP). The party is described variously as [[Right-wing politics|right-wing]],<ref>\n<!--start bundle-->*{{Cite news|url=http://www.theolivepress.es/spain-news/2018/07/25/spains-new-pp-leader-seeks-to-move-the-party-back-to-its-roots/ |title=Spain's new PP leader seeks to move the party 'back to its roots'|work=The Olive Press |date = 25 August 2018}}\n*{{Cite news|url=http://www.rtve.es/noticias/20140116/vox-partido-ortega-lara-propone-acabar-modelo-autonomico/851241.shtml|title=Vox, el partido de Ortega Lara, propone acabar con el modelo auton\u00f3mico |date=16 January 2014 |work=RTVE.es|access-date=25 November 2018|language=es-ES}}\n*{{Cite news|url=https://www.periodistadigital.com/periodismo/tv/2018/10/09/vox-extrema-derecha-ferreras-verstrynge-salvini-le-pen-lasexta-abascal.shtml|title=Ferreras llama a Verstrynge para que advierta del peligro de VOX, pero el gur\u00fa podemita le chafa la tarde: 'No son extrema derecha'|last=Rodr\u00edguez|first=Antonio|date=9 October 2018|access-date=25 November 2018|language=es}}\n*{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/mundo/noticias-internacional-46063487|title=Vox, el partido pol\u00edtico que quiere \"hacer Espa\u00f1a grande otra vez\"|last=Hedgecoe|first=Guy|date=2 November 2018|work=BBC News Mundo|access-date=25 November 2018|language=en-GB}}\n<!--end bundle-->\n</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last= de Prada|first=Juan Manuel de Prada|url=https://www.abc.es/opinion/abci-voxeando-201810130622_noticia.html|title=Voxeando|date=13 October 2018|work=ABC|language=es|access-date=14 January 2019}}</ref> [[Right-wing populism|right-wing populist]],<ref name=\"Slate\">{{cite news|last=Loucaides |first=Darren |title=Will Bannonism Play in Spain? |work=[[Slate (magazine)|Slate]] |url=https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2018/07/vox-party-in-spain-could-bring-right-wing-populist-wave-with-help-from-steve-bannon.html |date=2 July 2018 |access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=Gonz\u00e1lez-Enr\u00edquez|first=Carmen|date=14 February 2017|title=The Spanish Exception: Unemployment, inequality and immigration, but no right-wing populist parties|url=http://www.css.ethz.ch/content/dam/ethz/special-interest/gess/cis/center-for-securities-studies/resources/docs/Elcano-The%20Spanish%20Exception,%20Unemployment,%20Inequality%20and%20Immigration,%20but%20no%20Right-Wing%20Populist%20Parties.pdf|journal=Elcano Royal Institute|volume=|pages=34|quote=Vox could be described as the first attempt to form a modern right-wing populist party in Spain, with no echoes of the Francoist period. Rather than bank on Francoist nostalgia, the party aimed to attract right-wing voters dissatisfied with Partido Popular policies.|via=elcano}}</ref> or [[Far-right politics|far-right]].<ref name=fieldrodriguezteruel2019 /><ref>{{cite news|last=Regu\u00e9 |first= J\u00falia|title=Radiograf\u00eda de la extrema derecha en Catalunya |work= El Peri\u00f3dico |url= https://www.elperiodico.com/es/politica/20180819/extrema-derecha-catalunya-6970471 |date=19 August 2018|access-date=4 September 2018|language=ES}}<br>{{cite news|last1=Barriaux|first1=Marianne |last2=Villalobos|first2=Alvaro|title=Spain's far-right gains visibility in Catalonia crisis |url=https://www.thelocal.es/20171015/spains-far-right-gains-visibility-in-catalonia-crisis |work=The Local |date=15 October 2017|access-date=29 May 2018|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{cite news|last= Precedo|first=Jos\u00e9 |title=Vox: la ultraderecha irrelevante en las urnas agita los juzgados |url=https://www.eldiario.es/politica/Vox-derecha-extrema-prospera-juzgados_0_718828397.html |work=[[eldiario.es]] |date=17 December 2017|access-date=18 April 2018|language=es}}<br/>{{cite news|last=Minder |first= Raphael |url= https://www.nytimes.com/2018/03/27/world/europe/spain-catalonia-carles-puigdemont-extradition.html|title= Arrest of Catalan Leader Tests Spain, Separatists and E.U.|date=27 March 2018|work=The New York Times|accessdate=18 April 2018|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{cite news|last=|first= |title=Spain: No country for old fascists |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/spain-politics-far-right-podemos-rajoy-pp-populism-vox/ |work=Politico Europe |date=26 December 2016 |accessdate=29 May 2018|language=en-US}}<br>{{cite news|last=|first= |title=Spain proves sterile ground for far-right parties |url=http://www.dw.com/en/spain-proves-sterile-ground-for-far-right-parties/a-39057276 |work=Deutsche Welle |date=31 May 2017|language=en|accessdate=29 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n[[File:Acto de Vox en Vistalegre (44248349125).jpg|thumb|left|[[Javier Ortega Smith]] giving a speech in 2018 in [[Palacio Vistalegre|Vistalegre]].]]\n\nVox was founded on 17 December 2013,<ref>{{cite web|last=|first= |title=Pol\u00edtica de privacidad de VOX Espa\u00f1a |archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20140717024137/https://www.voxespana.es/index.php/aviso-legal |archive-date = 17 July 2014|url= https://www.voxespana.es/aviso-legal/ |website=voxespana.es/aviso-legal | publisher = Aviso Legal |language =es|date=|access-date=}}</ref> and publicly launched at a press conference in [[Madrid]] on 16 January 2014<ref>{{cite news|last1=Quintero|first1=L.F.|last2=Alonsof|first2=Mariano |url=http://www.libertaddigital.com/espana/politica/2014-01-14/nace-el-partido-politico-de-abascal-y-ortega-lara-1276508230/|title=Nace Vox, el partido pol\u00edtico de Santiago Abascal y Ortega Lara|work=Libertad Digital|date=14 January 2014|accessdate=16 March 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"Reuters1\">{{cite news|last=O'Leary|first=Elisabeth|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2014/01/16/us-spain-politics-idUSBREA0F1HM20140116|title=Spanish ruling party rebels launch new conservative party|date=16 January 2014|work=[[Reuters]]|accessdate=18 April 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> as a split from the People's Party. This schism was interpreted as an offshoot of \"neocon\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Fern\u00e1ndez|first=Guillermo |title=Vox abre la puerta|work=ctxt.es|quote=Vistalegre dibuja a Vox como la expresi\u00f3n de que una parte de la derecha \u201cneocon\u201d espa\u00f1ola se ha desgajado de la nave nodriza del Partido Popular|url=https://ctxt.es/es/20181010/Politica/22215/vox-vistalegre-guillemro-fernendez-programa-inmigracion-aborto-eutanasia.htm|date=10 October 2018}}</ref> or \"[[social conservatism|social conservative]]\"<ref>{{Cite book|first=Anja|last=Hennig|first2=Madalena|last2=Meyer-Resende|title=Bedingungen der Aktivierung von moralpolitischen Konflikten|isbn=978-3-658-11792-4|others=In: Ines-Jacqueline Werkner y Oliver Hidalgo (Eds.)|doi=10.1007/978-3-658-11793-1|pages=304\u2013305|publisher=[[Springer Publishing|Springer]]|year=2016}}</ref> PP party members. The party platform sought to rewrite the constitution to abolish regional autonomy and parliaments.<ref name=\"Reuters1\" /> Several of their promoters (for example: [[Alejo Vidal-Quadras Roca|Alejo Vidal-Quadras]], [[Jos\u00e9 Antonio Ortega Lara]] or [[Santiago Abascal]]) had been members of the platform \"reconversion.es\" that issued a manifesto in 2012 vouching for the recentralization of the State.<ref name=casals2019pp>{{Cite journal|url=https://www.politicaprosa.com/catalunya-i-la-espana-viva-de-vox/|journal=Pol\u00edtica&Prosa|date=1 April 2019|first=Xavier|last=Casals|issue=5|author-link=Xavier Casals i Meseguer|title=Catalunya i 'la Espa\u00f1a viva' de Vox}}</ref> Vidal-Quadras was proclaimed as the first chairman in March 2014.<ref>{{Cite web|work=Cr\u00f3nica Global|url=https://cronicaglobal.elespanol.com/politica/vox-elige-a-vidal-quadras-como-su-primer-presidente_5576_102.html|title=Vox elige a Vidal-Quadras como su primer presidente|date=8 March 2014}}</ref>{{refn|group=n.|Vidal Quadras later left the party after the political failure at the European election and his unability to impose his stances in the party. He would argue in 2018 that the party shifted from a \"[[liberal conservative]], [[europeanist]], and reformist\" proposal (represented by himself), to a \"Nationalist, revisionist, euroesceptic and confessional\" one.<ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://www.elperiodico.com/es/politica/20181101/quien-es-quien-vox-7093336|title=Las caras y los apoyos de Vox|journal=[[El Peri\u00f3dico de Catalunya|El Peri\u00f3dico]]|date=1 November 2018}}</ref>}}\n\nThe initial funding, totalling nearly 972,000 euros, came from individual money transfers by supporters of the [[People's Mujahedin of Iran]] (MEK).<ref name=casals2019pp /><ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2019/04/27/spains-vox-party-hates-muslims-except-the-ones-who-fund-it-mek-ncri-maryam-rajavi-pmoi-vidal-quadras-abascal/|journal=[[Foreign Policy]]|date=27 April 2019|title=Spain's Vox Party Hates Muslims\u2014Except the Ones Who Fund It|first=Sohail|last=Jannessari|first2=Darren|last2=Loucaides}}</ref>\n\nVox ran for the first time in the [[2014 European Parliament election in Spain|2014 European elections]] but narrowly failed to win a seat in the [[European Parliament]].<ref>{{cite news|last=|first= |title= Tristeza y decepci\u00f3n en Vox tras los resultados de las Elecciones Europeas |url=http://www.libertaddigital.com/espana/2014-05-26/tristeza-y-decepcion-en-vox-tras-los-resultados-de-las-elecciones-europeas-1276519600/ |work=Libertad Digital |language =es |date=26 May 2014|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2014 the party elected Santiago Abascal, one of the founders, as new President, and [[Iv\u00e1n Espinosa de los Monteros]], also a founder, as General Secretary. Eleven members of the National Executive Committee were also elected.\n\nThe party participated in the [[2015 Spanish general election|2015]] and the [[2016 Spanish general election|2016]] elections, but did not do well, scoring 0.23% and 0.20% of votes respectively.\n\nAfter the [[2017 Catalan independence referendum|Catalan referendum]] of 2017 and the start of a [[Spanish constitutional crisis]], Vox opted to not participate in the [[2017 Catalan regional election|Catalan regional elections of 2017]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.elplural.com/politica/2017/11/03/vox-el-21d-es-fruto-de-un-pacto-oculto-entre-rajoy-y-los-golpistas|title=VOX: \"El 21D es fruto de un pacto oculto entre Rajoy y los golpistas\"|last=Paradinas|first=Marcos|date=3 November 2017|work=[[elplural.com]]|access-date=18 April 2018|language=es}}</ref> After the [[Catalan declaration of independence]], the party sued the [[Parliament of Catalonia]] and several independentist politicians<ref>{{cite news|last=Garc\u00eda |first=Jes\u00fas |title=El TSJ catal\u00e1n admite la querella de Vox por rebeli\u00f3n contra Puigdemont|url=https://elpais.com/ccaa/2017/10/11/catalunya/1507707978_302026.html|work=El Pa\u00eds|date=11 October 2017|accessdate=30 August 2018|language=es}}</ref> and increased a 20% in forty days the number of members.<ref name=\":1\">{{cite news|url=http://www.publico.es/politica/afiliacion-partido-ultraderechista-vox-aumenta-20-40-dias.html|title=La afiliaci\u00f3n al partido ultraderechista VOX aumenta un 20% en 40 d\u00edas|work=P\u00fablico|accessdate=18 April 2018|language=es-ES}}</ref>\n\nOn 10 September 2018 Vox enlisted an independent legislator in the [[Assembly of Extremadura|regional parliament of Extremadura]] (who had dropped out of the PP parliamentary group) as party member.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.regiondigital.com/noticias/extremadura/298894-los-ex-populares-juan-antonio-morales-y-antonio-pozo-se-incorporan-a-vox.html |work=Regi\u00f3n Digital|language=es-ES|date=10 September 2018|accessdate=19 November 2018|title=Los ex 'populares' Juan Antonio Morales y Antonio Pozo se incorporan a Vox}}</ref> On 2 December 2018 they won 12 parliamentary seats in the [[2018 Andalusian regional election|Andalusian regional election]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-46422036 |title=Spain far-right Vox party gains foothold in Andalusia election |work=BBC News |date=3 December 2018}}</ref> entering a [[Parliament of Andalusia|regional parliament]] for the first time. It supported the coalition regional government by Ciudadanos and the Popular Party. With this result, Vox was also given a first seat in the [[Senate of Spain]], which was taken by [[Francisco Jos\u00e9 Alcaraz]].<ref>{{cite news |title=\u00bfQui\u00e9n es Francisco Jos\u00e9 Alcaraz, el primer senador de Vox? |url=https://www.20minutos.es/noticia/3566552/0/perfil-francisco-jose-alcaraz-vox-senador/ |accessdate=21 February 2019 |work=20 Minutos |date=19 February 2019 |language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\nThe party obtained 10.26% of votes in the [[April 2019 Spanish general election|April 2019 general election]], electing 24 Deputies and entering the [[Congress of Deputies]] for the first time in its history.<ref>[https://elpais.com/elpais/2019/04/29/inenglish/1556533756_984774.html Vox enters Congress for the first time but falls short of expectations] in elpais.com</ref> Later, the party entered for its first time in the [[European Parliament]] with 6.2% of the votes and 3 [[Member of the European Parliament|eurodeputies]], which after [[Brexit]] became 4. After this election, the party joined the [[European Conservatives and Reformists]] group and the [[Alliance of Conservatives and Reformists in Europe]].<ref name=\"ECR\" /> In the [[November 2019 Spanish general election|second general election of the year]] in November, Vox came third and increased its number of deputies from 24 to 52.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Jones |first1=Sam |title=Spain election: grand coalition ruled out as far-right Vox surges |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/nov/11/spain-election-grand-coalition-ruled-out-far-right-vox-surges |accessdate=11 November 2019 |work=The Guardian |date=11 November 2019}}</ref> It was the most-voted party in the [[Region of Murcia]] and the autonomous city of [[Ceuta]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Vox gana las elecciones en Murcia y Ceuta |url=https://www.elplural.com/politica/vox-gana-las-elecciones-en-murcia-y-ceuta_227542102 |accessdate=14 December 2019 |work=El Plural |date=10 November 2019 |language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\n== Ideology ==\nVox has been described as a Far-right party within the subset of the radical-right family.<ref name=ferreira /> Unlike other European radical right parties, its discourse relies relatively less in populism and more on nationalism.<ref name=ferreira /> It mixes nationalism and nativism with an authoritarian vision of society.<ref name=ferreira>{{Cite journal|last=Ferreira|first=Carles|date=2019|title=Vox como representante de la derecha radical en Espa\u00f1a: un estudio sobre su ideolog\u00eda|journal=Revista Espa\u00f1ola de Ciencia Pol\u00edtica|volume=51|language=es|issue=51|pages=73\u201398|doi=10.21308/recp.51.03|issn=2173-9870|doi-access=free}}</ref> Its economic agenda is neoliberal.<ref name=ferreira />\n\nStarting with a focus in economically liberal stances and [[Political unitarism|recentralization]] proposals, the focus of their message shifted towards stances compatible with European [[right-wing populism]],<ref name=\"casals\">{{cite journal|last=Casals|first=Xavier|author-link=Xavier Casals|date=21 April 2015|title=Vox y su campa\u00f1a contra la inmigraci\u00f3n masiva|url=http://www.elmanifiesto.com/articulos.asp?idarticulo=5047|journal=ElManifiesto.com}}</ref> endorsing anti-Islam as well as [[criticism of multiculturalism]] and criticizing [[immigration]] from Muslim countries,<ref>{{cite news|last=Balcarce|first=Luis|title=PERIODISTA DIGITAL ENTREVISTA AL CAMERUN\u00c9S DEL PARTIDO DE SANTIAGO ABASCAL |work=periodistadigital.com|quote=Bertrand Ndongo (Vox): \"Espa\u00f1a no deber\u00eda permitir la invasi\u00f3n de los musulmanes\"|url=https://www.periodistadigital.com/politica/partidos-politicos/2019/04/17/bertrand-ndongo-entrevista-negro-vox-espana-orgullo-santiago-abascal.shtml|date=17 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Sosa|first=Carlos |title=Abascal (Vox): \"No es lo mismo un inmigrante hispanoamericano que la inmigraci\u00f3n de los pa\u00edses isl\u00e1micos\"|work=eldiario.es|quote=Santiago Abascal alert\u00f3 a los presentes acerca de \u201cese 4% de musulmanes que hay en Espa\u00f1a y que, para algunos, puede resultar una minor\u00eda simp\u00e1tica\u201d. Su advertencia fue muy concreta: \u201cNo queremos que se conviertan en un problema\u201d.|url=https://www.eldiario.es/canariasahora/sociedad/VIDEO-Abascal-Vox-hispanoamericano-inmigracion_0_761874455.html|date=17 April 2018}}</ref> but at the same time promoting immigration from countries of Latin America in order to repopulate Spain.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.laopiniondezamora.es/zamora/2019/01/21/vox-apela-inmigracion-buena-atajar/1138744.html|title=Vox apela a \"la inmigraci\u00f3n buena\" para atajar la despoblaci\u00f3n en Zamora|first=La Opini\u00f3n de|last=Zamora|website=www.laopiniondezamora.es}}</ref> Their view of [[European Union]] is that of a [[Euroscepticism|soft euroscepticism]], arguing that Spain should make no [[sovereignty]] concessions to the EU, because they consider Spanish sovereignty to reside in the Spanish [[nation]] alone.<ref name=\"euro\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.larazon.es/espana/vox-quiere-reformar-europa-y-no-cree-en-la-actual-deriva-federalista-CE22158093|title=El discurso de Vox en Europa|last=Mac\u00edas|first=C. S.|date=2019-03-01|website=La Raz\u00f3n|language=es-ES|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-11-11}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{cite news|last=Abascal |first=Santiago |author-link= Santiago Abascal|url=http://www.libertaddigital.com/opinion/santiago-abascal/cadiz-covadonga-y-bruselas-77185/ |title=C\u00e1diz, Covadonga y Bruselas |work=Libertad Digital |date=8 November 2015|accessdate=21 July 2018|language=es-ES|quote=Porque estamos convencidos de que naci\u00f3n y soberan\u00eda son conceptos \u00edntimamente relacionados. Si somos soberanos es porque somos una Naci\u00f3n y no tenemos derecho a entregar lo que hemos recibido de nuestros mayores. Espa\u00f1a debe estar en Europa pero sin complejos, reivindicando el papel hist\u00f3rico, industrial y agr\u00edcola que merecemos. No debemos ser vasallos de Merkel ni de Tsipras. Ni camareros de Merkel ni paganos de las propinas de Tsipras. Las Cortes de C\u00e1diz proclamaron que la Naci\u00f3n espa\u00f1ola era libre e independiente y que no pod\u00eda ser patrimonio de ninguna familia o persona. Proclamaron asimismo que la soberan\u00eda reside esencialmente en la Naci\u00f3n, que es la \u00fanica que tiene derecho a establecer sus leyes fundamentales. Esta declaraci\u00f3n de soberan\u00eda ha sido una constante en toda nuestra historia constitucional.}}</ref> They propose to eliminate Spain's [[Autonomous communities of Spain|autonomous communities]].<ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://cronicaglobal.elespanol.com/politica/vox-fenomeno-mediatico-real_200221_102.html|journal=Cr\u00f3nica Global|title=Vox: \u00bffen\u00f3meno medi\u00e1tico o real?|date=17 December 2018|first=Mar\u00eda Jes\u00fas|last=Ca\u00f1izares}}</ref> In addition, they seek the return of [[Gibraltar]] to full Spanish sovereignty.<ref>[https://edition.cnn.com/2018/12/03/europe/spain-far-right-vox-andalucia-intl/index.html Spain's Vox party wins seats as far-right party surges for first time since Franco], [[CNN]], December 3, 2018</ref>\n\nVox is considered [[antifeminism|antifeminist]],<ref>{{cite news|last=Jones |first=Sam |title=Far right victories in Andaluc\u00eda send shockwave through Spanish politics |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/dec/09/far-right-andalucia-seville-vox-party-shockwave-spanish-politics |work=The Guardian |date=9 December 2018|access-date=9 December 2018}}</ref> and wants to repeal the gender violence law,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://elpais.com/politica/2018/12/03/actualidad/1543828526_382772.html|title=Derogar la ley de violencia de g\u00e9nero y otros planes de Vox contra el feminismo|first1=Pilar|last1=\u00c1lvarez|first2=Isabel|last2=Vald\u00e9s|date=3 December 2018|work=El Pais|access-date=9 December 2018}}</ref> which they see as \"discriminant against one of the sexes\" and replace it with a \"family violence law that will afford the same protection to the elderly, men, women and children who suffer from abuse\".<ref name=\"elpaisen\">{{cite news| last = Arroyo |first= Jorge Rodriguez |url=https://elpais.com/elpais/2018/12/03/inenglish/1543832942_674971.html|title=Far-right Spanish political party Vox: What are its policies?|date=3 December 2018|work=El Pais}}</ref>\n\nThe party pleads for the closure of fundamentalist mosques as well as the arrest and expulsion of extremist imams.<ref name=\"elpaisen\" /> Vox has openly called for the deportation of tens of thousands of Muslims from Spain.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thejc.com/news/world/as-spain-elects-its-first-far-right-mps-since-franco-party-leader-santiago-abascal-inquisition-years-1.483635|title=As Spain elects its first far-right MPs since Franco, the party's leader invokes the Inquisition years|website=[[The Jewish Chronicle]]|date=2 May 2019}}</ref> In 2019, the party's leader demanded a [[Reconquista]] or reconquest of Spain,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thenational.ae/world/europe/spain-s-far-right-makes-election-gains-using-anti-muslim-sentiment-1.855172|title=Spain's far-right makes election gains using anti-Muslim sentiment|website=[[The National (Abu Dhabi)]]|date=29 April 2019}}</ref> explicitly referencing a new expulsion of Muslim immigrants from the country.<ref>{{Cite journal|journal=[[The Times]]|title=Spain's far right eyes role as kingmaker in April elections|first=Kenza|last=Bryan|date=9 December 2018|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/spains-far-right-eyes-role-as-kingmaker-in-april-elections-7znlb6mx5}}</ref>\n\nAccording to [[Xavier Casals]], the warlike [[ultranationalism]] in Vox, unifying part of its ideology up to this point, is identified by the party with a [[palingenetic]] and biological vision of the country, the so-called \"''Espa\u00f1a Viva''\", but also with a Catholic-inspired culture.<ref name=casals20190119>{{Cite journal|url=http://agendapublica.elpais.com/vox-habla-sobre-vox-tres-libros-para-conocer-el-partido/|journal=Agenda P\u00fablica|date=19 January 2019|first=Xavier|last=Casals|author-link=Xavier Casals i Meseguer|title=Vox habla sobre Vox. Tres libros para conocer el partido|quote= Su ideario parece hallarse a\u00fan en construcci\u00f3n y tiene como eje vertebrador un ultranacionalismo b\u00e9lico asociado a la \u201cReconquista\u201d o a una \u201cCovadonga 2.0\u201d,  El partido lo identifica con una visi\u00f3n biol\u00f3gica y palingen\u00e9tica de la patria, la \u201cEspa\u00f1a viva\u201d, pero tambi\u00e9n con una cultura de inspiraci\u00f3n cat\u00f3lica.}}</ref> The party discourse has also revived the myth of the ''Antiespa\u00f1a'' (\"Anti-Spain\"), an umbrella term created in the 1930s by the domestic ultranationalist forces to designate the (inner) \"Enemies of Spain\".<ref name=mellon /><ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://www.elsaltodiario.com/historia/ha-vuelto-la-antiespana-vox-y-su-violencia-discursiva|journal=El Salto|title=Ha vuelto la Antiespa\u00f1a. Vox y su violencia discursiva|first=Marina |last=Segovia Vara|first2=Arnau|last2=Fern\u00e1ndez Pasalodos|date=18 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nAccording to Guillermo Fern\u00e1ndez V\u00e1zquez, Vox's discourse, which he described as \"economically'' anti-statist and neoliberal\" as well as \"morally'' authoritarian\", is similar to [[J\u00f6rg Haider]]'s [[FP\u00d6]] or [[Jean Marie Le Pen]]'s [[National Front (France)|National Front]] from the 1980s, thus likening the emergence of the party to an archaic stage of current radical right parties, more worried about the need to modernize their image than Vox; the later's approach to cultural issues would be in line with old school Spanish nationalist parties, restricting the scope of \"culture\" to \"language and tradition\".<ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://www.vozpopuli.com/altavoz/cultura/toros-derecha-vox-morante-calamaro-abascal_0_1239177065.html|journal=Voz P\u00f3puli|title=Morante, Calamaro y Abascal: \u00bfson los toros el nuevo rock and roll?|date=24 April 2019|first=V\u00edctor|last=Lenore}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|journal=[[CTXT]]|title=Vox, la extrema derecha de siempre|date=24 April 2019|url=https://ctxt.es/es/20190424/Politica/25776/Guillermo-Fernandez-Vazquez-Vox-programa-electoral-Abascal-neoliberalismo.htm#.XMDCQDZXL7g.twitter|first=Guillermo|last=Fern\u00e1ndez V\u00e1zquez|quote=A tenor de lo que muestra el programa, cultura es para Vox lengua y tradici\u00f3n, siguiendo el viejo lema de los partidos nacionalistas.}}</ref>\n\nVox openly endorses the State of Israel. The party has also appealed to conspiracy theories invoking the figure of Jewish philanthropist [[George Soros]] as mastermind behind Catalan separatism and the alleged \"Islamization\" of Europe.<ref>{{Cite journal|date=2 May 2019|journal=[[Tablet Mag]]|url=https://www.tabletmag.com/jewish-news-and-politics/284204/spains-pro-israel-far-right-party|first=Alejandro|last=Baer|title=The Rise of Spain's Pro-Israel, Far-Right Party}}</ref>  Vox has also featured some former neo-Nazis in party cadres and lists;<ref>{{Citation |url=https://www.lasexta.com/el-muro/antonio-maestre/historico-ultra-condenado-prision-asalto-blanquerna-encuentra-sitio-vox_201905025ccb1ef30cf2a0854cddfb42.html|work=[[La Sexta]]|date=2 May 2015|first=Antonio|last=Maestre|author-link=Antonio Maestre|title=Un hist\u00f3rico ultra condenado a prisi\u00f3n por el asalto a Blanquerna, en Vox}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|journal=[[ABC (Spain)|ABC]]|url=https://www.abc.es/espana/madrid/abci-pasado-nazi-candidato-alcala-henares-201905070024_noticia.html|date=7 May 2015|title=El pasado nazi de un candidato de Vox en Alcal\u00e1 de Henares}}</ref> some of them have been expelled from the party or have resigned.<ref>{{cite news|last=P\u00e9rez|first=Sergio |title=El n\u00famero 7 de Vox en Alcal\u00e1 renuncia por su nexo con una organizaci\u00f3n nazi|work=La Vox de Asturias|quote=Seg\u00fan informa Vox Alcal\u00e1 de Henares en un comunicado, Bonito ya ha presentado ante la Junta Electoral de Zona un \u00abescrito de renuncia a formar parte de dicha candidatura y a su acta de concejal electo\u00bb en el caso de que la obtuviera.|url=https://www.lavozdeasturias.es/noticia/actualidad/2019/05/13/numero-7-vox-alcala-renuncia-nexo-organizacion-nazi/00031557759589903293196.htm|date=13 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Redacci\u00f3n|first=Redacci\u00f3n |title=Vox expulsa al abogado Jos\u00e9 Mar\u00eda Ruiz Puerta por haber presidido la asociaci\u00f3n CEDADE|work=Alerta Nacional|quote=Tanto a Ortega Smith como a Roc\u00edo Monasterio les ha faltado tiempo para desvincularse de Ruiz Puerta. Sostienen que nunca ha militado ni pertenecido a Vox, lo que desdice lo que \u00e9l mismo ha publicado en redes sociales y tambi\u00e9n lo que manifest\u00f3 en \u201cAlt News\u201d. En el espacio radial dirigido y conducido por Santiago Fontenla sostuvo que \u00e9l ten\u00eda \u201cacceso directo\u201d a Abascal y daba por consumada su incorporaci\u00f3n a ese proyecto pol\u00edtico.|url=https://www.alertanacional.es/vox-expulsa-al-abogado-jose-maria-ruiz-puerta-por-haber-presidido-la-asociacion-cedade/|date=13 April 2019}}</ref> In November 2018, during a party event in Murcia, the party leader [[Santiago Abascal]] defined his party as \"[[antifascist]], antinazi and anticommunist\".<ref>{{cite news|last=G\u00f3mez|first=David |title=Abascal: \"Para callarnos nos tendr\u00e1n que meter en la c\u00e1rcel\"|work=La Verdad|quote=Santiago Abascal [...]defini\u00f3 a su formaci\u00f3n como \u00abantifascista, antinazi\u00bb|url=https://www.laverdad.es/murcia/abascal-callarnos-meter-20181115011216-ntvo.html|date=15 November 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Electoral performance==\n===Cortes Generales===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:97%; text-align:left;\"\n|-\n| colspan=\"10\" align=\"center\"| [[Cortes Generales]]\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" width=\"75\"| Election\n! colspan=\"5\"| Congress\n! colspan=\"2\"| Senate\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Leading candidate\n! rowspan=\"2\"| {{abbr|Gov.|Government}}\n|-\n! width=\"70\"| Votes\n! width=\"35\"| %\n! width=\"25\"| #\n! Seats\n! width=\"35\"| +/\u2013\n! Seats\n! width=\"35\"| +/\u2013\n|-\n! [[2015 Spanish general election|2015]]\n| 58,114\n| 0.2\n| 15th\n| {{Composition bar|0|350|hex={{Vox (political party)/meta/color}}}}\n| [[File:Arrow Blue Right 001.svg|10px]]0\n| {{Composition bar|0|208|hex={{Vox (political party)/meta/color}}}}\n| [[File:Arrow Blue Right 001.svg|10px]]0\n| rowspan=\"4\"| [[Santiago Abascal]]\n| style=\"background:#ddd; text-align:center;\"| No seats\n|-\n! [[2016 Spanish general election|2016]]\n| 47,182\n| 0.2\n| 13th\n| {{Composition bar|0|350|hex={{Vox (political party)/meta/color}}}}\n| [[File:Arrow Blue Right 001.svg|10px]]0\n| {{Composition bar|0|208|hex={{Vox (political party)/meta/color}}}}\n| [[File:Arrow Blue Right 001.svg|10px]]0\n| style=\"background:#ddd; text-align:center;\"| No seats\n|-\n! [[April 2019 Spanish general election|Apr-2019]]\n| 2,688,092\n| 10.3\n| 5th\n| {{Composition bar|24|350|hex={{Vox (political party)/meta/color}}}}\n| [[File:Green Arrow Up Darker.svg|10px]]24\n| {{Composition bar|0|208|hex={{Vox (political party)/meta/color}}}}\n| [[File:Arrow Blue Right 001.svg|10px]]0\n| style=\"background:#ffc; text-align:center;\"| New election\n|-\n! [[November 2019 Spanish general election|Nov-2019]]\n| 3,656,979\n| 15.1\n| 3rd\n| {{Composition bar|52|350|hex={{Vo